        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Baltics against Georgia</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-5-2.jpg" alt="Baltics against Georgia" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania have <a href="https://www.vm.ee/en/news/foreign-minister-tsahkna-bans-11-georgian-officials-entering-estonia" target="_blank">imposed</a> sanctions on Georgia‚Äôs ruling officials, including influential oligarch Bidzina Ivanishvili and Interior Minister Vakhtang Gomelauri, in response to the violent suppression of anti-government protests in Tbilisi. These officials are now barred from entering the three Baltic states because of ‚Äútheir participation in serious human rights violations by aggressively suppressing legitimate protests,‚Äù Estonia‚Äôs foreign ministry stated.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Estonian Foreign Minister Margus Tsahkna criticized the ruling party for lying to its citizens and suppressing their rights, emphasizing that the use of disproportionate force against peaceful demonstrations violates human rights. Newly appointed EU foreign policy chief Kaja Kallas <a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/estonia-latvia-lithuania-baltic-countries-sanctions-georgian-officials-protests-violence-georgia-eu-accession-enlargement/" target="_blank">warned</a> that Georgia‚Äôs democratic backsliding would have ‚Äúdirect consequences‚Äù for its EU aspirations.‚Äã</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
