          France's Prime Minister Michel Barnier was <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20241204-live-french-government-faces-collapse-as-historic-no-confidence-vote-approaches" target="_blank">ousted</a> after a no-confidence vote, the first since 1962, with 331 MPs against his government. This collapse leaves President Emmanuel Macron seeking a new prime minister to secure a working majority in the fractured National Assembly, complicating his remaining two years in office. Opposition leaders, like Mathilde Pinot of France Unbowed, have called for early presidential elections, but Macron dismissed this as "political fiction." This turmoil may delay France's defense budget and impact military support for Ukraine, as Defense Minister S√©bastien Lecornu noted. Macron is expected to address the situation with the nation on Thursday evening.</p>
